---
id: weegloo-api-endpoints
type: rule
title: Weegloo API Base URLs (for development code)
description: >
  CMA, CDA, Upload, ACMA, ACDA base URLs, Swagger links, and MCP vs direct API usage.
  Must be followed when calling Weegloo API via fetch, axios, etc. in project code.
---

rules:
  - section: AI Agent vs application code (mandatory)
    items:
      - **AI Agent (Cursor, Claude, etc.)** must **not** call these HTTP APIs directly. Use **Weegloo MCP tools** only.
      - **Application / development code** (frontend, backend, scripts) may call the APIs using the base URLs and paths documented below.
      - APIs are for **implementation in project code**; agents integrate via **MCP**, not raw REST calls.

  - section: Base URL by API Type (never guess or infer)
    items:
      - Weegloo APIs include **CMA**, **CDA**, **Upload**, and when the app manages its own members, **ACMA** and **ACDA** instead of CMA/CDA for those flows.
      - **CMA** (Content Management API): Read, create, update, delete. Base URL: `https://dev-cma.weegloo.com`
      - **CDA** (Content Delivery API): Cache-based, read-only. Base URL: `https://dev-cda.weegloo.com`
      - **Upload**: File uploads. Base URL: `https://dev-upload.weegloo.com`
      - **ACMA** (App Content Management API): Use when the app uses **its own member management** instead of Weegloo’s default model. In that case use **ACMA instead of CMA** for the relevant operations. Base URL: `https://dev-acma.weegloo.com`
      - **ACDA** (App Content Delivery API): Same scenario—**app-managed members**. Use **ACDA instead of CDA** for delivery/read paths that map to that model. Base URL: `https://dev-acda.weegloo.com`
      - API paths typically use `/v1/...`, e.g. `https://dev-cda.weegloo.com/v1` for CDA.

  - section: Swagger (OpenAPI) documentation per API
    items:
      - **CMA**: `https://dev-cma.weegloo.com/v1/swagger`
      - **CDA**: `https://dev-cda.weegloo.com/v1/swagger`
      - **Upload**: `https://dev-upload.weegloo.com/v1/swagger`
      - **ACMA**: `https://dev-acma.weegloo.com/v1/swagger`
      - **ACDA**: `https://dev-acda.weegloo.com/v1/swagger`

  - section: CMA vs CDA selection (standard Weegloo member model)
    items:
      - Most web services only need **read** access when content is managed in Weegloo Console. Use **CDA** in that case.
      - CMA supports full CRUD; CDA is preferable for read-only use (cache-optimized).
      - Do not confuse CMA and CDA. Use CDA for read-only delivery; CMA for management operations.

  - section: ACMA / ACDA vs CMA / CDA (app-managed members)
    items:
      - Most web services only need **read** access, since content create/update/delete is managed in Weegloo Console. Use **CDA** or **ACDA** in that case.
      - CMA/ACMA supports read, create, update, and delete, but CDA is preferable for read-only use due to its cache-based design.
      - Do not confuse CMA/ACMA and CDA/ACDA. Use CDA/ACDA for read-only, CMA/ACMA for management operations.
      - When the product uses **app-owned member management** (not the default Weegloo member flow), **do not use CMA/CDA** for those features—use **ACMA** and **ACDA** as documented in Swagger and product docs.
      - **ACMA** replaces **CMA** for that integration style; **ACDA** replaces **CDA** for the corresponding delivery/read usage.

  - section: CDA requirements (Delivery Access Token)
    items:
      - CDA requires a **Delivery Access Token** (and ACDA its equivalent when using that API—follow Swagger and env conventions for the project).
      - For **market / WebHosting template** apps, store values in **`./env.js`** only: `window.__ENV__ = { ... }`. Use **`DELIVERY_ACCESS_TOKEN`** for the Delivery Access Token (not a “hidden secret” in this pattern—it is expected in `env.js` so installers can swap it after copying the template to their Space).
      - Typical keys alongside the token: `WEEGLOO_CDA_BASE_URL`, `WEEGLOO_SPACE_ID`, `WEEGLOO_LOCALE`. The running app should read **only** `window.__ENV__` for these (see `weegloo-web-hosting-rules`).

  - section: Common Mistakes to Avoid
    items:
      - Do not infer or guess URLs. Use only the base URLs listed in this rule.
      - Wrong: `https://dev-cda-weegloo.com` (wrong host pattern), using CMA base URL for CDA traffic.
      - Correct: For CDA content fetch, use `https://dev-cda.weegloo.com/v1/spaces/{spaceId}/...`.

  - section: Base URL quick reference
    items:
      - CMA: `https://dev-cma.weegloo.com`
      - CDA: `https://dev-cda.weegloo.com`
      - Upload: `https://dev-upload.weegloo.com`
      - ACMA: `https://dev-acma.weegloo.com`
      - ACDA: `https://dev-acda.weegloo.com`
